t. Subsequent chapters explore the potentially democratic and even anarchic forces of digital filmmaking, the influences of hypertext and other new media, the increased role of the viewer in arranging and manipulating the chronology of a film, and the role of new punk cinema in plotting a course beyond the postmodern. The book examines a range of films, including The Blair Witch Project, Time Code, Run Lola Run, Memento, The Celebration, Gummo, and Requiem for a Dream.New Punk Cinema is ideal for classroom use at the undergraduate and graduate levels, as well as for film scholars interested in fresh approaches to the emergence of this vital new turn in cinema.Key FeaturesOffers a comprehensive examination of the term 'new punk' cinema.Provides several new approaches for the study of digital cinema.Includes close analysis of several key new punk films and directors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aChaudhuri, Shohini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDugdale, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaggi, Silvio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalligan, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarper, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsaacs, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLessard, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcRoy, Jay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendik, Xavier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRombes, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/